1. Overview University of Tartu Institute of Computer Science graduation theses requirements and criteria;
2. Recommendations for Estonian-language academic writing;
3. The research topic selection and preparation of a work plan;
4. Introducing one's topic at a discussion seminar together with getting and giving feedback;
5. Instructions for completing a literature review;
6. The use of citations and references;
7. Quotations and summaries, citation systems;
8. Plagiarism, the causes of plagiarism and prevention of it with the help of electronic plagiarism detection methods;
10. Instructions for making a good defence presentation;
11. Pre-defence rehearsal together with giving and receiving feedback.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the knowledge on master thesis writing requirements and criteria at the Institute of Computer Science; to get an overview of possible research methodologies; help resolving possible questions arising during the thesis writing; to learn the terms and the language connected to the speciality; to learn using efficiently the language maintenance related resources; to develop critical attitude towards text creation; to practice presentation skills for the defence of the master thesis; to learn on how to get and how to give feedback to work by fellow students.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, the student: 1) has the basic and background knowledge for performing a successful research; 2) can justify the choice of the methodology for one's master thesis and to perform an analysis; 3) is able to bring out basics for good master's thesis writing (structuring, spelling, referencing and citing, writing up the thesis); 4) is able to describe several ways of giving and receiving feedback and corresponding best practices; 5) can describe the characteristics of a good presentation of the thesis at defence.
